PMID== 1437068
TI  == complement activation by lipopolysaccharides purified from gram-negative bacteria isolated from infected root canals.
AB  == the purpose of the present study was to investigate the complement activation by  lipopolysaccharides purified from porphyromonas (bacteroides) endodontalis, veillonella parvula, and fusobacterium nucleatum isolated from infected root canals. the rate of consumption of the c3t component of the complement increased  remarkably when lipopolysaccharides of more than 10 micrograms were added.
